Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, thinly slice @tomato{1}(thinly sliced) into rounds; season with salt and pepper. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}(trimmed); cut into bite-size pieces.

Place @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and half the @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce} in separate #serving vessels{}. Present family style along with @sourdough bread{4%slice}, @sliced turkey breast{8%ounce}, @sliced mild cheddar cheese{2%slice}, and tomato for everyone to build their own sandwiches.

> You'll cook the melts in the next step!

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Carefully add sandwiches (for 4 servings, work in batches; wipe out pan between batches and add more olive oil as needed). Cook, gently pressing with a #spatula{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{}, until cheese melts and bread is golden, ~{2-4%minutes} per side, adding another drizzle of olive oil when flipping.

> TIP: Lower heat and cover with lid if sandwiches begin to brown too quickly.

In a #large bowl{}, toss lettuce with remaining dressing.

Halve turkey melts on a diagonal; divide between plates. Serve with potato wedges and salad on the side.

> TIP: Fill your sandwich with some salad for added crunch!